# ROBOPRO Architecture Rules

## Three-Layer Isolation

- `core/` -- pure TypeScript, NO imports from `react`, `next`, `three`, `zustand`
- `lib/stores/` -- Zustand stores, may import from `core/` interfaces only
- `app/` + `components/` -- React/Next.js UI, imports from stores and core interfaces

## Module Structure

- `core/mcu/` -- Virtual MCU (avr8js wrapper, pin state machine)
- `core/components/` -- Simulated hardware (motors, sensors, drivers, power)
- `core/physics/` -- Deterministic engines (kinetic, electrical)
- `core/simulation/` -- Orchestration (game loop, signal bus, wiring, registry)
- `lib/stores/` -- Zustand state stores
- `app/` -- Next.js pages and layouts
- `components/` -- React UI components (scene, editor, controls, wiring)

## Import Direction

```
UI → State → Core    ✅
Core → State          ❌
Core → UI             ❌
State → UI            ❌
```

## Naming

- Interfaces: `I` prefix (`IComponent`, `IMicrocontroller`)
- Stores: `use` prefix (`useSimulationStore`)
- Components: PascalCase files (`.tsx`)
- Core classes: PascalCase files (`.ts`)

## DI Mandate

Core classes accept interfaces via constructor, never instantiate concrete dependencies internally.

## Single Source of Truth

Each piece of state lives in exactly one Zustand store. Components subscribe; they never duplicate state.
